            </spirit:reset>
            <spirit:field>
              <spirit:name>CHN_EN</spirit:name>
              <spirit:description> Channel Enable:\n0 : Disable the channel.\n1 : Enable the channel. </spirit:description>
              <spirit:bitOffset>0</spirit:bitOffset>
              <spirit:bitWidth>1</spirit:bitWidth>
              <spirit:access>read-write</spirit:access>
            </spirit:field>
            <spirit:field>
              <spirit:name>LLIST_EN</spirit:name>
              <spirit:description> Link list Enable, only available for full DMA  channel.\n0 : Disable the link list.\n1 : Enable the link list. </spirit:description>
              <spirit:bitOffset>4</spirit:bitOffset>
              <spirit:bitWidth>1</spirit:bitWidth>
              <spirit:access>read-write</spirit:access>
            </spirit:field>
            <spirit:field>
              <spirit:name>LLIST_CFG_VALID</spirit:name>
              <spirit:description> If "LLIST_EN" asserted, active high indicates  Link list configure valid.\n0 : Link list configure in-valid. DMA controller  need obtain link list configure information by link list pointer.\n1 : link list configure information valid. DMA  controller would continue to complete the node and clear this bit.\nNote: Strongly recommend to observe only.  Carefully writing to this bit, which may cause DMA crashed. If had to do so,  pause this channel before changing. </spirit:description>
              <spirit:bitOffset>8</spirit:bitOffset>
              <spirit:bitWidth>1</spirit:bitWidth>
              <spirit:access>read-write</spirit:access>
            </spirit:field>
            <spirit:field>
              <spirit:name>CHN_PRIORITY</spirit:name>
              <spirit:description> Channel Request Priority. Four level of Priority  supported as list :\n2'b00 : Lowest priority.\n2'b01 : Secondary lowest priority.\n2'b10 : Tertiary lowest priority.\n2'b11 : Highest priority. </spirit:description>
              <spirit:bitOffset>12</spirit:bitOffset>
              <spirit:bitWidth>2</spirit:bitWidth>
              <spirit:access>read-write</spirit:access>
            </spirit:field>
            <spirit:field>
              <spirit:name>AHB_BURST_SEL</spirit:name>
              <spirit:description> AMBA Burst Select.\n2'b00 : INCR8;\n2'b01 : INCR4; \n2'b10 : INCR16; \n2'b11 : INCR16; </spirit:description>
              <spirit:bitOffset>16</spirit:bitOffset>
              <spirit:bitWidth>2</spirit:bitWidth>
              <spirit:access>read-write</spirit:access>
            </spirit:field>
            <spirit:field>
              <spirit:name>ERR_TYPE_STATUS</spirit:name>
              <spirit:description> Error Configure , which would be  cleared when "ERR_INT_STATUS" cleared:\n4'b0001 : Addr Wrap Error Configure;\n4'b0010 : Request Mode Error Configure;\n4'b0100 : Length Error Configure;\n4'b1000 :Unalign Error Configure;\n1 gt;  Addr wrap error configure\nSet  wrap enable in standard DMA channel.\n2 gt;  Request mode error configure\nReq_mode==2  or 3 in in standard DMA channel.\n3 gt;  Length Error Configure\nd gt;  Frag_len==0;\ne gt;  Blk_len==0;\nf gt;  FULL DMA channel,trsc_len==0;\n4 gt;  Unalign Error Configure\nc gt;  Src unsigned error\na1 gt;  address unalign in halfword width\nerror=(src_data_size[1:0]==1) amp; amp;(src_addr[0] =0)\na2 gt;  address unalign and trsf_step unalign in word width\nerror=(src_data_size[1:0]==2) amp; amp;(src_addr[1:0] =0)\namp; amp;(src_trsf_step =4)\nd gt;  dest unsigned error\nb1 gt;  address unalign in halfword width\nerror=(dst_data_size[1:0]==1) amp; amp;(dst_addr[0] =0)\nb2 gt;  address unalign and trsf_step unalign in word width\nerror=(dst_data_size[1:0]==2) amp; amp;(dst_addr[1:0] =0)\namp; amp;(dst_trsf_step =4) </spirit:description>
              <spirit:bitOffset>20</spirit:bitOffset>
              <spirit:bitWidth>4</spirit:bitWidth>
              <spirit:access>read-only</spirit:access>
            </spirit:field>
          </spirit:register>
