            </spirit:field>
            <spirit:field>
              <spirit:name>BLK_LEN_REC_H</spirit:name>
              <spirit:description> Block counter[16:15], update after each fragment  done;\nNote: Normally configured to 2'b0. Only to be  configured other value during state retention after wake up </spirit:description>
              <spirit:bitOffset>17</spirit:bitOffset>
              <spirit:bitWidth>2</spirit:bitWidth>
              <spirit:access>read-write</spirit:access>
            </spirit:field>
            <spirit:field>
              <spirit:name>LLIST_END</spirit:name>
              <spirit:description> Link list end flag. Active only when "LLIST_EN"  asserted. </spirit:description>
              <spirit:bitOffset>19</spirit:bitOffset>
              <spirit:bitWidth>1</spirit:bitWidth>
              <spirit:access>read-write</spirit:access>
            </spirit:field>
            <spirit:field>
              <spirit:name>SRC_ADDR_FIX_EN</spirit:name>
              <spirit:description> Source Address Fix Enable:\n0 : Disable Source Address Fix mode.\n1 : Enable Source Address Fix mode.\nActive High would make source address fixed within the  fragment, while "FRAG_STEP" and "BLK_STEP" would be applied to address after  fragment done; </spirit:description>
              <spirit:bitOffset>20</spirit:bitOffset>
              <spirit:bitWidth>1</spirit:bitWidth>
              <spirit:access>read-write</spirit:access>
            </spirit:field>
            <spirit:field>
              <spirit:name>DEST_ADDR_FIX_EN</spirit:name>
              <spirit:description> Selection of the side using Address Fix mode.\n0 : Disable Destination Address Fix mode.\n1 : Enable Destination Address Fix mode.\nActive High would make destination address fixed within the  fragment, while "FRAG_STEP" and "BLK_STEP" would be applied to address after  fragment done; </spirit:description>
              <spirit:bitOffset>21</spirit:bitOffset>
              <spirit:bitWidth>1</spirit:bitWidth>
              <spirit:access>read-write</spirit:access>
            </spirit:field>
            <spirit:field>
              <spirit:name>ADDR_WRAP_EN</spirit:name>
              <spirit:description> Active High enable Address-wrapping for ring  buffer. The next address of DMA jumps to "WRAP_START_ADDR" address when the  current address matches "WRAP_END_ADDR" address:\n0 : Disable address wrap mode.\n1 : Enable address wrap mode. "WRAP_START_ADDR"  and "WRAP_END_ADDR" would be used to limit the address space of either Source  or Destination. </spirit:description>
              <spirit:bitOffset>22</spirit:bitOffset>
              <spirit:bitWidth>1</spirit:bitWidth>
              <spirit:access>read-write</spirit:access>
            </spirit:field>
            <spirit:field>
              <spirit:name>ADDR_WRAP_SEL</spirit:name>
              <spirit:description> Selection of the side using Address wrap mode.\n0 : Address wrap on Source.\n1 : Address wrap on Destination.\nOnly one side of a DMA channel can activate  address-wrapping mode at a time. </spirit:description>
              <spirit:bitOffset>23</spirit:bitOffset>
              <spirit:bitWidth>1</spirit:bitWidth>
              <spirit:access>read-write</spirit:access>
            </spirit:field>
            <spirit:field>
              <spirit:name>REQ_MODE</spirit:name>
              <spirit:description> Request mode, For Full DMA channel:\n2'b00 : Fragment;\n2'b01 : Block;\n2'b10 : Transaction;\n2'b11 : Link List; </spirit:description>
              <spirit:bitOffset>24</spirit:bitOffset>
              <spirit:bitWidth>2</spirit:bitWidth>
              <spirit:access>read-write</spirit:access>
            </spirit:field>
            <spirit:field>
              <spirit:name>SWT_MODE</spirit:name>
              <spirit:description> Data Switch mode selection.\n2'b00 : ABCD = gt; ABCD;\n2'b01 : ABCD = gt; DCBA\n2'b10 : ABCD = gt; BADC;\n2'b11 : ABCD = gt; CDAB </spirit:description>
              <spirit:bitOffset>26</spirit:bitOffset>
              <spirit:bitWidth>2</spirit:bitWidth>
              <spirit:access>read-write</spirit:access>
            </spirit:field>
            <spirit:field>
              <spirit:name>DEST_SIZE</spirit:name>
