            <spirit:bitOffset>4</spirit:bitOffset>
            <spirit:bitWidth>1</spirit:bitWidth>
            <spirit:access>read-write</spirit:access>
          </spirit:field>
          <spirit:field>
            <spirit:name>bck_lrck_0</spirit:name>
            <spirit:description> configure extend cycles of bck after data transfer is finished.\nVoice_Mode:: each sample takes wlen + tx_bck_lrck BCLK cycle. \nAudio_Mode:: each sample takes 2*(wlen + tx_bck_lrck) BCLK cycle. 2 times than Voice  </spirit:description>
            <spirit:bitOffset>5</spirit:bitOffset>
            <spirit:bitWidth>5</spirit:bitWidth>
            <spirit:access>read-write</spirit:access>
          </spirit:field>
          <spirit:field>
            <spirit:name>wlen_0</spirit:name>
            <spirit:description> i2s data length\n00: 16-bit\n01: 20-bit\n10: 24-bit\n11: 32-bit </spirit:description>
            <spirit:bitOffset>10</spirit:bitOffset>
            <spirit:bitWidth>2</spirit:bitWidth>
            <spirit:access>read-write</spirit:access>
          </spirit:field>
          <spirit:field>
            <spirit:name>lrck_pol_0</spirit:name>
            <spirit:description> configure LRCK polarity. \n0:: LEFT_H_RIGHT_L:    high level on LRCK means left channel, low level on LRCK means right channel. \n1:: LEFT_L_RIGHT_H:    high level on LRCK means right channel, low level on LRCK means left channel. \nNote: this bit should be set to '0' (LEFT_H_RIGHT_L) in voice mode. </spirit:description>
            <spirit:bitOffset>12</spirit:bitOffset>
            <spirit:bitWidth>1</spirit:bitWidth>
            <spirit:access>read-write</spirit:access>
          </spirit:field>
          <spirit:field>
            <spirit:name>bck_pol_0</spirit:name>
            <spirit:description> if Master Mode, invert BCLK out. if slave Mode, invert BCLK in.\n0:: NORMAL\n1:: INVERT </spirit:description>
            <spirit:bitOffset>13</spirit:bitOffset>
            <spirit:bitWidth>1</spirit:bitWidth>
            <spirit:access>read-write</spirit:access>
          </spirit:field>
          <spirit:field>
            <spirit:name>bckout_gate_0</spirit:name>
            <spirit:description> Sets the BckOut gating. This bit decide if aud intf continue to output BCK clock after data has been sent.\n0:: NO_GATE\n1:: GATED </spirit:description>
            <spirit:bitOffset>14</spirit:bitOffset>
            <spirit:bitWidth>1</spirit:bitWidth>
            <spirit:access>read-write</spirit:access>
          </spirit:field>
          <spirit:field>
            <spirit:name>rx_half_cycle_dly_0</spirit:name>
            <spirit:description> delayed Audio input data by half cycle.\n0:: NO_DLY\n1:: DLY </spirit:description>
            <spirit:bitOffset>15</spirit:bitOffset>
            <spirit:bitWidth>1</spirit:bitWidth>
            <spirit:access>read-write</spirit:access>
          </spirit:field>
          <spirit:field>
            <spirit:name>tx_lrck_half_cycle_dly_0</spirit:name>
            <spirit:description> delayed Audio LRCK by half cycle.\n0:: NO_DLY\n1:: DLY </spirit:description>
            <spirit:bitOffset>16</spirit:bitOffset>
            <spirit:bitWidth>1</spirit:bitWidth>
            <spirit:access>read-write</spirit:access>
          </spirit:field>
          <spirit:field>
            <spirit:name>rx_dly_0</spirit:name>
            <spirit:description> Indicates the delay between serial data in MSB and LRCK edge. \n2'b00:: ALIGN:    Digital audio in MSB is aligned with LRCLK edge. \n2'b01:: DLY_1:   Digital audio in MSB is 1 cycle delayed to LRCLK edge. \n2'b10:: DLY_2:   Digital audio in MSB is 2 cycle delayed to LRCLK edge. \n2'b11:: DLY_3:   Digital audio in MSB is 3 cycle delayed to LRCLK edge. </spirit:description>
            <spirit:bitOffset>17</spirit:bitOffset>
            <spirit:bitWidth>2</spirit:bitWidth>
            <spirit:access>read-write</spirit:access>
          </spirit:field>
          <spirit:field>
            <spirit:name>tx_dly_s_0</spirit:name>
            <spirit:description> ONLY for slave mode:: configure 1 cycle supplementary Tx delay. \n0:: NO_DLY:  No supplementary Tx delay. \n1:: DLY:         One Cycle supplementary Tx delay. </spirit:description>
            <spirit:bitOffset>19</spirit:bitOffset>
            <spirit:bitWidth>1</spirit:bitWidth>
            <spirit:access>read-write</spirit:access>
          </spirit:field>
          <spirit:field>
            <spirit:name>tx_dly_0</spirit:name>
            <spirit:description> configure the delay between serial data out MSB and LRCK edge. \n0:: ALIGN:           Digital audio out MSB is aligned with LRCLK edge. \n1:: DLY_1:          Digital audio out MSB is 1 cycle delayed to LRCLK edge </spirit:description>
            <spirit:bitOffset>20</spirit:bitOffset>
            <spirit:bitWidth>1</spirit:bitWidth>
            <spirit:access>read-write</spirit:access>
          </spirit:field>
          <spirit:field>
            <spirit:name>master_mode_0</spirit:name>
            <spirit:description> configure aud intf works in master mode (LRCLK and BCK timing signals are generated internally) or slave mode (LRCLK and BCK timing signals are generated externally).\n0:: SLAVE\n1:: MASTER </spirit:description>
            <spirit:bitOffset>21</spirit:bitOffset>
            <spirit:bitWidth>1</spirit:bitWidth>
            <spirit:access>read-write</spirit:access>
          </spirit:field>
          <spirit:field>
            <spirit:name>rx_serial_mode_0</spirit:name>
            <spirit:description> Configure serial aud intf mode. \n0:: I2S_PCM\n1:: VOICE\n2:: DAI\nWhen mode is set DAI, the bit Master Mode should be set to '1'. Data should be sent out on falling edge, which requires either Bclk_Pol = '0' and Half_Cycle_DLY = '1' or Bclk_Pol = '1' and Half_Cycle_DLY = '0'. Bits Tx_DLY and BCKOut_Gate must be configured to '0' and '1'. \nThe DAI mode must NOT be modified after aud intf is enabled.  </spirit:description>
            <spirit:bitOffset>22</spirit:bitOffset>
            <spirit:bitWidth>3</spirit:bitWidth>
            <spirit:access>read-write</spirit:access>
          </spirit:field>
          <spirit:field>
            <spirit:name>tx_serial_mode_0</spirit:name>
            <spirit:description> Configure serial aud intf mode. \n0:: I2S_PCM\n1:: VOICE\n2:: DAI\nWhen mode is set DAI, the bit Master Mode should be set to '1'. Data should be sent out on falling edge, which requires either Bclk_Pol = '0' and Half_Cycle_DLY = '1' or Bclk_Pol = '1' and Half_Cycle_DLY = '0'. Bits Tx_DLY and BCKOut_Gate must be configured to '0' and '1'. \nThe DAI mode must NOT be modified after aud intf is enabled.  </spirit:description>
            <spirit:bitOffset>25</spirit:bitOffset>
            <spirit:bitWidth>3</spirit:bitWidth>
            <spirit:access>read-write</spirit:access>
          </spirit:field>
          <spirit:field>
            <spirit:name>tx_off_0</spirit:name>
            <spirit:description> Disable aud intf Tx functions. Important:: if you want to do record only, you must set this bit otherwise aud intf state machine will not start. \n0:: TX_ON:    Both Tx Rx enabled. \n1:: TX_OFF:   Rx enabled only, Tx disabled. </spirit:description>
            <spirit:bitOffset>28</spirit:bitOffset>
            <spirit:bitWidth>1</spirit:bitWidth>
            <spirit:access>read-write</spirit:access>
          </spirit:field>
          <spirit:field>
            <spirit:name>tx_mode_0</spirit:name>
            <spirit:description> Configure mono or stereo format for Audio data out:\n2'b00:: STEREO_STEREO:  stereo input from DMA, stereo output to pin. \n2'b01:: MONOL_STEREO_DUPLI:   mono channel L input from DMA, stereo output duplicate in both channels to pin. \n2'b10:: MONOR_STEREO_DUPLI:  mono channel R input from DMA, stereo output duplicate in both channels to pin. \n2'b11:: MONO_IN_MONO_OUT\nFuntion mono input from DMA, stereo output in left channel to pin, can be implemented by setting aud intf_tx_cfg_ch[1] or aud intf_tx_cfg_ch[0] disable.\nWhen works in DAI, or DSD mode, always select "00" mode STEREO_STEREO. </spirit:description>
            <spirit:bitOffset>29</spirit:bitOffset>
            <spirit:bitWidth>2</spirit:bitWidth>
            <spirit:access>read-write</spirit:access>
          </spirit:field>
          <spirit:field>
            <spirit:name>i2s_enable_0</spirit:name>
            <spirit:description> enable i2s interface </spirit:description>
            <spirit:bitOffset>31</spirit:bitOffset>
            <spirit:bitWidth>1</spirit:bitWidth>
            <spirit:access>read-write</spirit:access>
          </spirit:field>
        </spirit:register>
        <spirit:register>
          <spirit:name>aud_intf_i2s_cfg1</spirit:name>
          <spirit:addressOffset>0x20</spirit:addressOffset>
          <spirit:size>32</spirit:size>
          <spirit:reset>
            <spirit:value>0x10200000</spirit:value>
            <spirit:mask>0xffffffff</spirit:mask>
          </spirit:reset>
          <spirit:field>
            <spirit:name>swap_chlr_1</spirit:name>
            <spirit:description> Swap Channel L and Channel R.[0]\n[0] for output channel swap, 0: left, 1:right\n[1] for input channel swap, 0: left, 1: right </spirit:description>
            <spirit:bitOffset>0</spirit:bitOffset>
            <spirit:bitWidth>2</spirit:bitWidth>
            <spirit:access>read-write</spirit:access>
          </spirit:field>
          <spirit:field>
            <spirit:name>tx_data_half_cycle_dly_1</spirit:name>
            <spirit:description> delayed Audio data out by half cycle.\n0:: NO_DLY\n1:: DLY </spirit:description>
            <spirit:bitOffset>2</spirit:bitOffset>
            <spirit:bitWidth>1</spirit:bitWidth>
            <spirit:access>read-write</spirit:access>
          </spirit:field>
          <spirit:field>
            <spirit:name>lsb_1</spirit:name>
            <spirit:description> When high, the output data format is with the least significant bit first.\n0:: MSB\n1:: LSB </spirit:description>
            <spirit:bitOffset>3</spirit:bitOffset>
            <spirit:bitWidth>1</spirit:bitWidth>
            <spirit:access>read-write</spirit:access>
          </spirit:field>
          <spirit:field>
            <spirit:name>right_justified_1</spirit:name>
            <spirit:description> right justified mode. </spirit:description>
            <spirit:bitOffset>4</spirit:bitOffset>
            <spirit:bitWidth>1</spirit:bitWidth>
            <spirit:access>read-write</spirit:access>
          </spirit:field>
          <spirit:field>
            <spirit:name>bck_lrck_1</spirit:name>
            <spirit:description> configure extend cycles of bck after data transfer is finished.\nVoice_Mode:: each sample takes wlen + tx_bck_lrck BCLK cycle. \nAudio_Mode:: each sample takes 2*(wlen + tx_bck_lrck) BCLK cycle. 2 times than Voice  </spirit:description>
            <spirit:bitOffset>5</spirit:bitOffset>
            <spirit:bitWidth>5</spirit:bitWidth>
            <spirit:access>read-write</spirit:access>
          </spirit:field>
          <spirit:field>
            <spirit:name>wlen_1</spirit:name>
            <spirit:description> i2s data length\n00: 16-bit\n01: 20-bit\n10: 24-bit\n11: 32-bit </spirit:description>
            <spirit:bitOffset>10</spirit:bitOffset>
            <spirit:bitWidth>2</spirit:bitWidth>
            <spirit:access>read-write</spirit:access>
          </spirit:field>
          <spirit:field>
            <spirit:name>lrck_pol_1</spirit:name>
            <spirit:description> configure LRCK polarity. \n0:: LEFT_H_RIGHT_L:    high level on LRCK means left channel, low level on LRCK means right channel. \n1:: LEFT_L_RIGHT_H:    high level on LRCK means right channel, low level on LRCK means left channel. \nNote: this bit should be set to '0' (LEFT_H_RIGHT_L) in voice mode. </spirit:description>
            <spirit:bitOffset>12</spirit:bitOffset>
            <spirit:bitWidth>1</spirit:bitWidth>
            <spirit:access>read-write</spirit:access>
          </spirit:field>
          <spirit:field>
            <spirit:name>bck_pol_1</spirit:name>
            <spirit:description> if Master Mode, invert BCLK out. if slave Mode, invert BCLK in.\n0:: NORMAL\n1:: INVERT </spirit:description>
            <spirit:bitOffset>13</spirit:bitOffset>
            <spirit:bitWidth>1</spirit:bitWidth>
            <spirit:access>read-write</spirit:access>
          </spirit:field>
          <spirit:field>
            <spirit:name>bckout_gate_1</spirit:name>
            <spirit:description> Sets the BckOut gating. This bit decide if aud intf continue to output BCK clock after data has been sent.\n0:: NO_GATE\n1:: GATED </spirit:description>
            <spirit:bitOffset>14</spirit:bitOffset>
            <spirit:bitWidth>1</spirit:bitWidth>
            <spirit:access>read-write</spirit:access>
          </spirit:field>
          <spirit:field>
            <spirit:name>rx_half_cycle_dly_1</spirit:name>
            <spirit:description> delayed Audio input data by half cycle.\n0:: NO_DLY\n1:: DLY </spirit:description>
            <spirit:bitOffset>15</spirit:bitOffset>
