          <spirit:field>
            <spirit:name>SEC_EFUSE_MAGIC_NUMBER</spirit:name>
            <spirit:description>Magic number, only when this field is 0x8800, the efuse programming command can be handle.\nSet the magic number right will lock the power switch and PGM enable.\nSo if SW want to program efuse memory, except open clocks and power, 2 other conditions must be met :\n(1) SEC_EFUSE_MAGIC_NUMBER =0x8800\n(2) PG_EN=1;\n(3) Switch the power right;</spirit:description>
            <spirit:bitOffset>0</spirit:bitOffset>
            <spirit:bitWidth>16</spirit:bitWidth>
            <spirit:access>read-write</spirit:access>
          </spirit:field>
