          <spirit:field>
            <spirit:name>VStsDone</spirit:name>
            <spirit:description>VStatus Done (VStsDone)\nThe core sets this bit when the vendor control access is done. This\nbit is cleared by the core when the application sets the New\nRegister Request bit (bit 25).\nValues:\n0x0 (INACTIVE): VStatus Done inactive\n0x1 (ACTIVE): VStatus Done active</spirit:description>
            <spirit:bitOffset>27</spirit:bitOffset>
            <spirit:bitWidth>1</spirit:bitWidth>
            <spirit:access>read-write</spirit:access>
          </spirit:field>
          <spirit:field>
            <spirit:name>VStsBsy</spirit:name>
            <spirit:description>VStatus Busy (VStsBsy)\nThe core sets this bit when the vendor control access is in progress\nand clears this bit when done.</spirit:description>
            <spirit:bitOffset>26</spirit:bitOffset>
            <spirit:bitWidth>1</spirit:bitWidth>
            <spirit:access>read-only</spirit:access>
          </spirit:field>
          <spirit:field>
            <spirit:name>NewRegReq</spirit:name>
            <spirit:description>New Register Request (NewRegReq)\nThe application sets this bit for a new vendor control access.\nValues:\n0x0 (INACTIVE): New Register Request not active\n0x1 (ACTIVE): New Register Request active</spirit:description>
            <spirit:bitOffset>25</spirit:bitOffset>
            <spirit:bitWidth>1</spirit:bitWidth>
            <spirit:access>read-write</spirit:access>
          </spirit:field>
          <spirit:field>
            <spirit:name>RegWr</spirit:name>
            <spirit:description>Register Write (RegWr) Set this bit for register writes, and clear it\nfor register reads.</spirit:description>
            <spirit:bitOffset>22</spirit:bitOffset>
            <spirit:bitWidth>1</spirit:bitWidth>
            <spirit:access>read-write</spirit:access>
          </spirit:field>
          <spirit:field>
            <spirit:name>RegAddr</spirit:name>
            <spirit:description>Register Address (RegAddr)\nThe 6-bit PHY register address for immediate PHY Register set\naccess. Set to 6'h2F for Extended PHY Register set access.</spirit:description>
            <spirit:bitOffset>16</spirit:bitOffset>
            <spirit:bitWidth>6</spirit:bitWidth>
            <spirit:access>read-write</spirit:access>
          </spirit:field>
          <spirit:field>
            <spirit:name>VCtrl</spirit:name>
            <spirit:description>UTMI+ Vendor Control Register Address (VCtrl) The 4-bit register\naddress a vendor defined 4-bit parallel output bus. Bits 11:8 of this\nfield are placed on utmi_vcontrol[3:0]. ULPI Extended Register\nAddress (ExtRegAddr) The 6-bit PHY extended register address.</spirit:description>
            <spirit:bitOffset>8</spirit:bitOffset>
            <spirit:bitWidth>8</spirit:bitWidth>
            <spirit:access>read-write</spirit:access>
          </spirit:field>
          <spirit:field>
            <spirit:name>RegData</spirit:name>
            <spirit:description>Register Data (RegData)\nContains the write data for register write.\nRead data for register read, valid when VStatus Done is set.</spirit:description>
            <spirit:bitOffset>0</spirit:bitOffset>
            <spirit:bitWidth>8</spirit:bitWidth>
            <spirit:access>read-write</spirit:access>
          </spirit:field>
